NARRATOR: Documentaries engage...

00:00:08.240 --> 00:00:10.800
[Background chatter]

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:14.410
CHARACTER: This place is my father's legacy 
that he left to me...

00:00:14.410 --> 00:00:16.600
...I'm doing my best to keep us afloat.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:17.900
NARRATOR: Enlighten...

00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:20.800
CHARACTER: There's like a long period of time 
where I felt so young...

00:00:20.800 --> 00:00:24.610
...I was like stuck being young.

00:00:24.700 --> 00:00:25.600
NARRATOR: Enrage...

00:00:39.400 --> 00:00:41.000
NARRATOR: They can be participatory...

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:42.100
...performative..

00:00:42.400 --> 00:00:43.800
...poetic.

00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:51.710
Documentaries change the way
we view the world around us...

00:00:51.710 --> 00:00:56.149
CHARACTER: It was a way of connecting

00:00:56.149 --> 00:01:00.900
me and my sister 
with the family that she had lost...

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:05.000
her mother, her father, her sisters, her brother...

00:01:05.200 --> 00:01:08.200
...nearly everyone that she loved in the world.

00:01:10.400 --> 00:01:12.300
NARRATOR:
...and transform the way we see ourselves.

00:01:12.800 --> 00:01:15.590
CHARACTER: Don't let one moment...

00:01:15.590 --> 00:01:17.900
not even one breath go by...

00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:21.600
without some sort of appreciation of it.

